festival.introText:
This is the original FeastyFest, which benefits local projects and charities through the work they do at their awesome festival with Feasty Community Projects.


FeastyFest provide foodies young and old with the opportunity to try unique and delicious items from across the south of England, as well as some entertaining live music to make it one big party!

faqs.question: When is FeastyFest 2023?
faqs.answer: FeastyFest takes place on Sunday 10th of September 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to FeastyFest?
faqs.answer:
Train

Sutton and Cheam stations are within easy walking distance of the festival site. There are also numerous local stations with easy access to the site via bus routes.

 

Driving

Please use postcode SM3 8BP, when navigating to the festival using a sat nav. As you approach the site you will see yellow event signs on your route, we ask you follow these as you approach your final destination. 

 

Parking Availability

Feasty fest runs a car park with parking for over 1000 cars via Netley Close off Nordan Road, there is plenty of space here for people’s cars when coming to the festival. DO NOT under any circumstances park on residential roads or in small closes where nearby residents live, this will disrupt the day to day life of local residents and we want all to enjoy the FeastyFest.

 

Bus Stop & Nearby Route

The Tilehurst road bus stop is right next to the festival site, it is accessible on the following routes: 151, 213, 613, 627.

faqs.question: Is FeastyFest Accessible?
faqs.answer:
We are proud to provide an accessible site for all and will help to accommodate any Feasters’ additional needs to ensure that everyone can enjoy the festival and all it has to offer.

We are working to make FeastyFest as accessible as possible. However, FeastyFest is an outdoor event in a park that could pose problems for mobility (particularly in wet weather).

Free tickets will be provided for carers and personal assistants for standard adult ticket holders with physical and mental difficulties. For those with child and teen tickets, a free carer or personal assistant ticket shall also be provided free of charge, but the child or teen must be accompanied by a paying adult ticket holder (such adult ticket holder may be the carer or personal assistant).

faqs.question: How much are FeastyFest tickets?
faqs.answer: Tickets start at £8 + booking fee for an adult ticket.

faqs.question: Will I need cash at FeastyFest?
faqs.answer: There are no cashpoints on site and all stands are predominantly card only with vendors providing a card payment option also, therefore FeastyFest do not recommend bringing large amounts of cash on site.

faqs.question: Is disabled parking available?
faqs.answer: Free disabled parking is Via Parkside Road of the Broadway in Cheam Village. Clear signage will direct blue badge holders to the disabled parking area. You must be in possession of a valid blue badge to gain access.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into FeastyFest?
faqs.answer: FeastyFest always has a huge selection of food and drink available for you so bringing food or alcohol onto site is prohibited. However, for young feasters including babies, we understand parents may wish to bring snacks for young children and jarred baby food to site and this is permitted.

faqs.question: What are the disabled features?
faqs.answer:
Accessible toilets throughout the site. 

Disabled Parking (you will need to have your blue badge on display). 

Stewards to help with any difficulties that may arise over the day.

faqs.question: Are payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Payment plan tickets are currently not on sale.
